  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 2, 1867, p. 119: "Eusebius, surnamed 
    Scholasticus, a Greek historian who lived about A.D. 400, for he is said to have been an eye-witness of the war of the Romans
    against Gainas, king of the Goths. He was a follower of Troilus, and wrote the history of the Gothic war, in hexamater verse, 
    in four books. His work is said to have been very popular at the time, but has not come down to us." (Socrat., H.E. vi, 6
    Niceph. H.E. xiii 6)</mads:note>
